          "description": "Came in for an 8 am appt and receptionist ignored us. When we asked to check in she told us to use the kiosk even though I\u2019d already pre-paid and checked in online. Upon further questioning she reluctantly booted up her computer, then told us that the provider was stuck in traffic. At 8:45 am the provider strolled in with a fresh coffee that he\u2019d evidently stopped for. At 8:55 we were finally seen, not even by the provider, but by an assistant. Finally, the provider came in, didn\u2019t even bother doing an exam, just referred us for x-ray. Also, the lights in the waiting area are painfully bright.\n\nIf it were any one of these things it wouldn\u2019t be a big deal, but taken together it\u2019s not a good sign. Will try one of the other Medrites next time I need Anthem-covered urgent care.",
